<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--MineRescue     07-22 0168</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Mine Rescue,0172</SECOND>
<HEAD>Workers Rescue Miner Trapped 12 Days in Tunnel</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CEBU CITY, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Workers rescued a copper miner who
survived by eating his shirt while trapped 12 days in a tunnel by a
mudslide, a mining company said.
   Atlas Consolidated Mining and Development Corp. said in a
statement that Roberto Lingao-Lingao was rescued Friday.
   He survived by eating his shirt a little at a time as fellow
miners inched their way 1,473 feet through mud and other debris to
reach him, the statement said.
   Lingao-Lingao, a former soldier with training in jungle
survival, became trapped in a tunnel after intermittent heavy rain
sent tons of mud cascading down a shaft on July 8, the company said.
   The mine is in the village of Lutupan, about 22 miles from Cebu
City and 350 miles southeast of Manila.
   Lingao-Lingao suffered ``mild disorientation and extreme
weakness,'' the mining company statement said, quoting the miner as
saying he spent most of his time underground sleeping to conserve
energy.
</TEXT>
