<FIRST>u a AM-ChurchGunman     07-22 0264</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Church Gunman,0270</SECOND>
<HEAD>Gunman Kills Two in Bible Study Class</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By ROBERT JABLON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A hooded gunman burst into a Bible study
class at a church Friday night, opening fire and killing two women
and wounding a man inside a chapel crowded with adults and
children, police said.
   The gunman ran into the Mount Olive Church of God in Christ and
opened fire as about 45 adults and children attended class at the
church that had a reputation for its anti-drug activism, said Sgt.
Frank Mena.
   One man, who was shot in the leg, was taken to California
Medical Center, Mena said. Identities of the dead were not
immediately known.
   ``We heard ... that this church is very anti-gang, anti-drug,''
Mena said. But he added it was unclear if the killings were
gang-related.
   No arrests were made and a search for the gunman was under way,
police said. The class participants remained inside the church more
than an hour after the 9:30 p.m. shooting.
   One woman whose whose children were inside the church at the
time of the attack said she was told the assailant wore black
clothing.
   ``The lady who drives the church bus called me,'' said Freddie
Willis whose twin 8-year-old daughters were inside the church
during the attack but were unharmed.
   ``She just told me someone dressed in black just came in and
shot up the church,'' she said.
   City fire spokesman Jim Wells said three ambulances were sent to
the scene of the shooting, an area of the city plagued by gang
activity.
</TEXT>
