<HEAD>Thunderstorms Strike West, South</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Thunderstorms and showers brought rain to much of the nation
early today, hours after Phoenix received its first rainfall in
nearly four months.
   Morning showers and thunderstorms extended over Arizona, New
Mexico, Colorado, Utah, eastern Nevada, northern Wyoming, western
Montana, Arkansas, east-central Missouri, central Illinois,
Indiana, western and northern Ohio, northwest Pennsylvania and
western New York.
   In the South, showers and thunderstorms dampened eastern West
Virginia, western Virginia, central and eastern South Carolina,
Georgia, Florida, Alabama and Mississippi. Showers fell over
south-central Texas.
   Heavier rainfall during the six hours ending at 2 a.m. EDT
included more than 1\ inches of rain at Jacksonville and an inch at
Douglas, Ariz.
   Meanwhile, one-hundredth of an inch of rain fell on Phoenix,
giving the city its first measurable rainfall since March 26.
   Today's forecast called for scattered showers and thunderstorms
over the central and eastern Gulf Coast, parts of the Tennessee and
Ohio valleys, the middle Mississippi Valley, the southern
two-thirds of the Appalachians, the middle and southern Atlantic
Coast, southern New England and the central and southern Rockies.
   Highs were expected to be in the 70s along the Pacific and New
England coasts and parts of Missouri and Wisconsin; in the 90s in
the middle Atlantic Coast, Florida, southern Texas, the southern
and central Rockies and the northern Plains; in the 100s in the
desert Southwest and interior valleys of California; and in the 80s
elsewhere.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 51
degrees at Marquette, Mich., to 97 degrees at Las Vegas.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 73 partly cloudy; Boston 65 foggy; Buffalo 70
foggy; Charleston, S.C. 78 fair; Cincinnati 73 partly cloudy;
Cleveland 70 foggy; Detroit 70 foggy; Miami 80 showers; New York 67
hazy; Pittsburgh 72 partly cloudy; Portland, Maine 57 fair;
Washington 78 hazy.
   _Central: Bismarck 66 fair; Chicago 68 foggy; Dallas-Fort Worth
73 fair; Denver 70 windy; Des Moines 64 fair; Indianapolis 70 fair;
Kansas City 67 partly cloudy; Minneapolis-St. Paul 65 fair;
Nashville 72 partly cloudy; New Orleans 77 fair; St. Louis 68 foggy.
   _West: Albuquerque 68 partly cloudy; Anchorage 58 showers; Las
Vegas 96 windy; Los Angeles 68 fair; Phoenix 84 showers; Salt Lake
City 78 cloudy; San Diego 69 cloudy; San Francisco 56 fair; Seattle
61 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 64 partly cloudy; Toronto 66 foggy.
