<FIRST>r i AM-Typhoon     07-22 0198</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Typhoon,0206</SECOND>
<HEAD>Rains Caused By Typhoon Hope Kill 24, Injure 1,000</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Torrential rains and floods caused by Typhoon
Hope have killed at least 24 people and injured 1,000 in eastern
China, an official report said Saturday, just days after Typhoon
Gordon took at least 17 lives.
   The Xinhua News Agency said up to 7{ inches of rain fell in
various counties of Fujian province during the 24 hours beginning 8
a.m. Friday.
   Torrents rushed down mountains and several rivers flooded,
destroying 4,000 houses and covering 8,150 acres of cropland, the
report said.
   It said one person was missing.
   Typhoon Hope came ashore late Thursday in Zhejiang province,
just north of Fujian, but no deaths were reported there.
   Typhoon Gordon swept into southeastern China's Guangdong
province on Tuesday. It killed 17 people and injured more than 100,
while 13 were reported missing. Heavy damage also was done to
crops, bridges, highways and telecommunications.
   Gordon first hit land Sunday in the Philippines, where it killed
32 people. It killed on person in Hong Kong on Tuesday, officials
said.
   Flooding has killed a total of 1,400 people throughout China
since early June, according to official reports.
