<SECOND>AM-BRF--Caning,0164</SECOND>
<HEAD>Teacher Reported to Cane 400 Boys</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Education officials said Saturday
they suspended an assistant high school teacher accused of
punishing 400 students by flogging them with a cane.
   The teacher at a boys' high school in Kuantan, about 150 miles
from Kuala Lumpur, caned the boys from three separate grades on
Monday, according to an unidentified student quoted by the state
news agency Bernama.
   He said the boys were not told what they had done wrong.
   Abdul Rahman Arshad, director-general of education, said the
government expected a report on the incident within a week. He said
the teacher, who was not identified, has been suspended.
   An unidentified staff member at the school told Bernama there
had been problems with discipline at the school. He said students
had been showing disrespect to teachers and neglecting to keep the
school tidy.
   Under Malaysian education laws, only male schoolchildren may be
caned.
