<HEAD>Three Jockeys Guilty of Fixing Races</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONG KONG (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A jury on Saturday found three Hong Kong
jockeys guilty of fixing races.
   Jockeys Tam Man-chau, Chan Yuk-pui, and Wong Yung-sang were
charged with businessman Bill Chan of conspiring to fix races
between 1984 and 1986.
   An eight-member High Court jury in this British colony handed
down Saturday's verdict. It failed to reach a verdict on the
businessman, who will be retried at a later date.
   All four defendants pleaded innocent.
