central Seoul.
   Police blocked the protesters with interlocked shields.
   Witnesses said Park Ho-kyu, 29, poured gasoline over his body
and set himself on fire during the clash. Park _ who suffered burns
on his hands, neck and chest _ was taken to a hospital, where he
was expected to recover.
   The man, who sold hats near the plush Lotte Hotel, and the other
vendors are enraged by a new government regulation that forbids
them to sell in downtown areas. The rule was designed to help keep
the city's streets clean.
