<DATELINE>HANOVER, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two East German men rammed their
car through border barriers Saturday in an attempt to flee their
communist homeland, police said.
   West German border police said a 20-year-old man managed to
climb out of the car and scale barriers to reach the West, but his
companion suffered serious injuries in the crash and remained
behind.
