<DOCNO> AP890722-0153 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-07-22-89 0106EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f AM-Kraft-Whitman     07-22 0340</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Kraft-Whitman,0354</SECOND>
<HEAD>New Presidents Named at Kraft, Whitman</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The president of Philip Morris Cos.' General
Foods division is moving to Whitman Corp., prompting a high-level
management change at Kraft General Foods, the nation's largest food
company, officials said Friday.
   Miles L. Marsh, who served in various positions at Kraft before
its takeover by New York-based Philip Morris last year, will move
to Whitman Sept. 1 as president and chief operating officer.
   Marsh will be succeeded as president at General Foods USA by
Richard P. Mayer, and James M. Kilts has been named president of
Kraft General Foods' Kraft USA unit.
   Marsh, 42, will oversee all of Chicago-based Whitman's
subsidiaries, including food-maker Pet Inc., Pepsi-Cola General
Bottlers, Hussmann Corp. and Midas International.
   ``We are all looking forward to working closely with him as we
take the next steps in our long-range plan to increase value for
our shareholders,'' Whitman chairman and chief executive officer,
Karl Bays, said in a statement Friday.
   In 1976, Marsh served as a consultant for McKinsey and Co. for
five years. He then served eight years with Dart &amp; Kraft in the
United States and London.
   He was named president of Kraft International in 1985 and later
was appointed president of the Operations and Technology Group of
Kraft, based in suburban Glenview.
   It is hoped his presence at Whitman will strengthen the
company's focus on consumer goods and services, Bays said.
   Mayer, former chairman and chief executive officer of Kentucky
Fried Chicken Worldwide, a unit of Pepsico Inc., will join General
Foods immediately.
   Mayer's experience in consumer products management spans more
than 20 years and includes both package goods and foodservice
operations in both a domestic and international framework, Kraft
said.
   Kilts, who was senior vice president of strategy and development
for Kraft General Foods, has two decades of experience with General
Foods and Kraft in product management and business development.
   He spearheaded the revitalization of Kraft Canada and was
instrumental in developing the plan for integrating Kraft and
General Foods, Kraft said.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
