<FIRST>d f PM-Eastern-Tickets     07-22 0106</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Eastern-Tickets,0112</SECOND>
<HEAD>Eastern Plan Gives Ticketholders Several Options</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Eastern</HEAD>
<HEAD>EDS: For Saturday PMs</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The proposed reorganization plan filed Friday by
Eastern Airlines specifies four options for consumers holding
Eastern tickets issued before the company's March 9 bankruptcy
filing:
   _Applying for a cash refund with interest.
   _Using the ticket for travel of equal value, with a free upgrade
to first class when space is available.
   _Using the ticket for travel of equal value, with the right to
buy a companion ticket for half the normal fare.
   _Exchanging the ticket for travel credits valued at 135 percent
of the ticket being exchanged.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
